  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1235",
  "title": "react-instantsearch release goals",
  "body": "With the work done by @Morhaus on instantsearch + react, we are on the road to releasing it.\n## Goals\n- provide a set of React components as a separate library (`react-instantsearch` in npm). With a beta testing phase.\n- allow people to reuse widget logic to create different implementation of our widgets (via HOC/connect-like in `react-instantsearch`)\n- the default behavior of widgets should be to keep the user refinements visible even if they are no more relevant (#962 #840 #1152 #1260)\n- allow people to manually feed some widget with data (example: \"I want a menu with those 5 colors\"), #1062 \n- change the API and/or implementation of some complex widgets (currentRefinementValues for example), check those `widget:nameOfWidget` labels in github\n- create a nice website to document the library, publish it at community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react\n- the website should be focused on widget pages and a guide with a progressive learning curve (much like the helper website)\n\nThe current working branch is in v2.\n\nI will create some issues and label them v2 so we can work on them.\n\n![a999adfe26ebc81a94754b364c4881b077ae695bd220d1a963142ef521df008b](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/18206414/ebf79764-7126-11e6-9520-97cae3d1db68.jpg)\n",
